    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The business logic of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CalculateFiscalYear",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function involves determining the fiscal year based on the input date. The workflow includes:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Extracting the year from the input date."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Applying business rules to adjust the year based on the fiscal year start month. For example, if the fiscal year starts in October, dates from January to September belong to the previous fiscal year, while dates from October to December belong to the current calendar year."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Returning the calculated fiscal year as an integer."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Scalar functions can be less efficient when used in large queries or within loops, as they are executed row-by-row. This can lead to performance bottlenecks in large datasets."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "To mitigate performance issues, consider using inline table-valued functions or incorporating the logic directly into queries if possible."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
